The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs 

 Higher education minister Sudarshan

 Roy Choudhury will discuss

 the upgrade of Bengal Engineering

 and Science University (Besu)

 with the teachers union on April 30. In a letter to chief secretary Amit Kiran Deb, the Union ministry of human resources development had asked the state government to hand over Besu as a precondition for the upgrade.

 Four people were arrested for

 selling paintbrushes made of

 mongoose hair in Chandni Chowk

 on Thursday. The raid was conducted

 by the state forest departments wildlife wing.

 Six passengers to New Delhi by an Air Deccan evening flight were not allowed to board the aircraft as they were late by five minutes. The passengers said they were held up in the registration queue.

 Five containers, with explosives and AK-series firearms, were seized at Calcutta port on Thursday. The containers, from Dar-es-Salaam, were sent by Nepal for the UN peacekeeping force in Tanzania. The consignment was rejected there and sent back to Nepal via Calcutta port. 




